article.description: — Tyrone Williams' 33 points led Old Dominion over Coastal Carolina 75-59 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 33, Old Dominion defeats Coastal Carolina 75-59
article.linkText: Williams scores 33, Old Dominion defeats Coastal Carolina 75-59
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- — Tyrone Williams' 33 points led Old Dominion over Coastal Carolina 75-59 on Saturday night. Williams also contributed five rebounds for the Monarchs (7-22, 3-14 Sun Belt Conference). Devin Ceaser scored 14 points and added five steals. R.J. Blakney had eight points. The Monarchs snapped a six-game slide. John Ojiako finished with 17 points and 13 rebounds for the Chanticleers (8-19, 5-11). Jacob Meyer added 16 points for Coastal Carolina. Braeden MacVicar also had eight points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
